Description: Wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian?) pottery cup or bowl; interior glazed black with three red lines painted in mid-wall; exterior: black band on upper wall, the reserved; inscription cut on exterior, on upper wall.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), temenos (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.365)
